{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012gfcdUkAVkTN9sw7EF2sGw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: add-field\n     3→description: Add a new field to a Django model and propagate to admin, serializer, and factory. Use when adding model fields or database columns.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Add Field\n     7→\n     8→Add a field to a Django model and propagate it to admin, serializer, and factory.\n     9→\n    10→## Usage\n    11→\n    12→```bash\n    13→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"model_name\": \"<Model>\", \"field_name\": \"<name>\", \"field_type\": \"<Type>\", \"field_args\": \"<args>\", \"factory_default\": \"<default>\"}'\n    14→```\n    15→\n    16→## Variables\n    17→\n    18→- **model_name**: Model class name (e.g. `Reservation`)\n    19→- **field_name**: New field name (e.g. `loyalty_tier`)\n    20→- **field_type**: Django field type (e.g. `CharField`)\n    21→- **field_args**: Field arguments (e.g. `max_length=20, default=\"bronze\"`)\n    22→- **factory_default**: Factory default value (e.g. `\"bronze\"`)\n    23→\n    24→Extract these from the user's request.\n    25→\n    26→## Gotchas\n    27→\n    28→- If jig exits non-zero, it prints the rendered templates to stderr. Use that output to apply changes manually.\n    29→- The recipe uses anchor-based patching. If the anchor pattern doesn't match the actual class definition, jig will fail. Fall back to manual editing using the stderr output.\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47551eeb-3c70-485c-809b-a96bee90398e","uuid":"6611559a-c552-4520-a58a-41647a2fdef2"}
